• Drilling Commencement: 3,000m RC drilling program (30 holes) started at Bullabulling Gold Project (100% owned).
  • Key Targets: Follow-up on high-grade gold intercepts including:
  • 2m @ 18.1 g/t Au from 34m
  • 12m @ 2.3 g/t Au from 53m
  • 4m @ 10.12 g/t Au from 32m.
  • Strategic Location: Adjacent to Minerals 260’s Bullabulling Gold Mine (2.3M oz resource).
  • Exploration Potential: Same mafic-ultramafic stratigraphy as neighboring mine extends into BMG’s tenure.
  • Assay Timeline: Results expected late July/early August 2025.
  • Infrastructure Advantage: Proximity to Coolgardie mining district with established transport and processing facilities.

No material capital markets or liquidity impacts identified (operational update only).

• Listing Change: Commenced trading on TSX Main Board (symbol: SXGC) on July 2, 2025; delisted from TSX Venture Exchange. ASX listing (symbol: SX2) remains unchanged.
  • Strategic Rationale: Enhances access to deeper capital markets, broader institutional investor base, and potential index inclusion opportunities.
  • Project Highlight: Controls Sunday Creek Gold-Antimony Project (60km north of Melbourne), with 12km strike length and 66 intersections >100 g/t AuEq x m.
  • Financial Position: Treasury of A$170m; commencing 200+ km drill program.

No material trading or capital markets actions required (no capital raising, no timetable events).

• Key Points:
  • Ownership Retention: Raiden retains 100% ownership of the Mt Sholl Ni-Cu-PGE Project after First Quantum Minerals (FQM) withdraws from the MOU.
  • Financial Benefit: Raiden receives A$135k for unmet drilling commitments (Stage 1), totaling A$385k cash from FQM under the MOU.
  • Work Acquired: Raiden gains full ownership of FQM's work, including ~2,466m drilling, geophysical surveys, engineering studies, and discovery of the Keel prospect (estimated A$2m spent by FQM).
  • Resource Potential: Mt Sholl has a JORC resource of 40Mt @ 0.45% Ni_Eq (1.17% Cu_Eq), with high-grade zones (5.8Mt @ 0.94% Ni_Eq). Open-pit potential and exploration upside noted.
  • Next Steps: Raiden evaluating development pathways, including regional opportunities, to maximize shareholder value.

Material Impact:
- Positive: No dilution from FQM earn-in; acquired data enhances project understanding at no cost.
- Neutral/Negative: Loss of potential partner may delay development funding.

Omitted: Operational details, board listings, and non-material JORC tables.

Exploration Results Announcement (Kokoseb Gold Project): - Key Highlights: - Best intercept to date: 50m at 12.00 g/t Au (including 1m at 528 g/t Au) in drill hole KRC437. - Multiple high-grade intercepts:
- 24m at 2.42 g/t Au
- 118.3m at 1.46 g/t Au (unconstrained intercept)
- 9.7m at 4.66 g/t Au (extending high-grade shoot).
- All mineralized zones remain open at depth/strike, indicating further resource growth potential.

  • Resource Impact:
  • Results will be included in upcoming Mineral Resource Estimate (MRE) scheduled for July 2025.

  • Project currently hosts 2.12Moz inferred gold resources (1.0 g/t Au cutoff).

  • Operational Context:

  • Kokoseb is located in Namibia (stable mining jurisdiction).
  • Discovery cost: <US$3/oz (industry-low).

Actionable Takeaways:
- High-grade results likely to positively impact resource upgrade and project economics.
- Potential catalyst: MRE update in July 2025 (watch for increased resource size/grade).
- Confirms continuity of mineralization, reducing geological risk.
